I"Å5<h2 id="control-structure-ifelse">Control Structure if/else</h2>

<p>La struttura di controllo <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">if/else</code> esegue unâ€™istruzione o un blocco di istruzioni se una condizione specificata come argomento di <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">if</code> risulta <em>true</em>. Se la condizione risulta <em>false</em> si eseguono le istruzioni del ramo <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">else</code></p>

<p><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Statements/if...else">MDN - ifâ€¦else</a></p>

<div class="language-js highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="k">if</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">condition1</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="p">{</span>
    <span class="c1">//code</span>
<span class="p">}</span> <span class="k">else</span> <span class="k">if</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">condition2</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="p">{</span>
    <span class="c1">//code</span>
<span class="p">}</span>
<span class="k">else</span> <span class="p">{</span>
    <span class="c1">//code</span>
<span class="p">}</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>La condizione espressa come argomento di <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">if</code> Ã¨ trattata come unâ€™espressione logica e quindi ritorna un boolean: <em>true/false</em>.</p>

<div class="language-js highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="cm">/*Utilizzo di operatori logici combinati al costrutto if/else*/</span>

<span class="kd">const</span> <span class="nx">maggioreEta</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">18</span><span class="p">;</span>
<span class="kd">const</span> <span class="nx">etaLuca</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">;</span>

<span class="k">if</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">etaLuca</span> <span class="o">&gt;</span> <span class="nx">maggioreEta</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="p">{</span>
    <span class="nx">console</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">log</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="dl">"</span><span class="s2">Luca Ã¨ maggiorenne</span><span class="dl">"</span><span class="p">);</span>
<span class="p">}</span> <span class="k">else</span> <span class="p">{</span>
    <span class="nx">console</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">log</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="dl">"</span><span class="s2">Luca non Ã¨ maggiorenne</span><span class="dl">"</span><span class="p">);</span>
<span class="p">}</span>
<span class="cm">/*
Luca non Ã¨ maggiorenne
*/</span>



<span class="cm">/* Boolean logic, trattano l'espressione come logica
AND     -&gt; &amp;&amp; : ritorna TRUE se tutte le condizioni sono VERE
OR      -&gt; || : ritorna TRUE se una condizione Ã¨ VERE
NOT     -&gt; !  : inverte il risultato dell'espressione logica
*/</span>

<span class="kd">const</span> <span class="nx">nome</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="dl">"</span><span class="s2">Luca</span><span class="dl">"</span><span class="p">;</span>
<span class="kd">const</span> <span class="nx">eta</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">15</span><span class="p">;</span>

<span class="k">if</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">eta</span> <span class="o">&lt;=</span> <span class="mi">13</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="p">{</span>
    <span class="nx">console</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">log</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">nome</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="dl">"</span><span class="s2"> Ã¨ un bambino</span><span class="dl">"</span><span class="p">);</span>
<span class="p">}</span> <span class="k">else</span> <span class="k">if</span> <span class="p">(</span> <span class="nx">eta</span> <span class="o">&gt;</span> <span class="mi">13</span> <span class="o">&amp;&amp;</span> <span class="nx">eta</span> <span class="o">&lt;=</span> <span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="p">{</span>
    <span class="nx">console</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">log</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">nome</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="dl">"</span><span class="s2"> Ã¨ un ragazzo</span><span class="dl">"</span><span class="p">);</span>
<span class="p">}</span>
 <span class="k">else</span>  <span class="p">{</span>
    <span class="nx">console</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">log</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">nome</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="dl">"</span><span class="s2"> Ã¨ un adulto</span><span class="dl">"</span><span class="p">);</span>
<span class="p">}</span>
<span class="cm">/*
Luca Ã¨ un ragazzo
*/</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<h2 id="ternary-operator">Ternary Operator</h2>

<p>Il Ternary Operator Ã¨ un costrutto condizionale inline.</p>

<p>Lâ€™operatore condizionale (ternary) Ã¨  lâ€™unico operatore JavaScript che necessitÃ  di tre operandi. Questo operatore Ã¨ frequentemente usato al posto del comando <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">if</code> per la sua sintassi concisa e perchÃ© fornisce direttamente un espressione valutabile.</p>

<p><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/it/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Operators/Operator_Condizionale">MDN - Operatore condizionale (ternary)</a></p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">(condition) ? (steatement1) : (steatement2);</code> : Se <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">condition</code> risulta <em>true</em> verrÃ  eseguito <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">steatement1</code> altrimenti <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">steatement2</code>.<br /></p>

<div class="language-js highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="cm">/* Ternary Operator */</span>
<span class="kd">var</span> <span class="nx">nome</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="dl">"</span><span class="s2">Marco</span><span class="dl">"</span><span class="p">;</span>
<span class="kd">var</span> <span class="nx">eta</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="dl">"</span><span class="s2">17</span><span class="dl">"</span><span class="p">;</span>

<span class="nx">eta</span> <span class="o">&gt;=</span> <span class="mi">18</span> <span class="p">?</span> <span class="nx">console</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">log</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">nome</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="dl">"</span><span class="s2"> puÃ² guidare</span><span class="dl">"</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="p">:</span> <span class="nx">console</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">log</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">nome</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="dl">"</span><span class="s2"> non puÃ² guidare</span><span class="dl">"</span><span class="p">);</span>

<span class="cm">/*
Marco non puÃ² guidare
*/</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Eâ€™ da preferire il <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">ternary operator</code> nei casi in cui si hanno due semplici statemeant da eseguire condizionati da unâ€™espressione altrettanto semplice. In questo caso risulta chiaro ed elegante.</p>

<h2 id="switch-statemeant">Switch statemeant</h2>

<p>Lâ€™ultimo costrutto condizionale Ã¨ <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">switch</code>.
Il comando <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">switch</code> valuta un espressione, confronta il valore dellâ€™espressione con ciascuna delle clausole <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">case</code> ed esegue i comandi (statements) associati alla clausola (case) che verifica il confronto.</p>

<p><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/it/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Statements/switch">MDN - switch</a></p>

<div class="language-js highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="k">switch</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">key</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="p">{</span>
    <span class="k">case</span> <span class="nx">value1</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="c1">//code</span>
        <span class="k">break</span><span class="p">;</span>
    <span class="k">case</span> <span class="nx">value2</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="c1">//code</span>
        <span class="k">break</span><span class="p">;</span>      
    <span class="nl">default</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="c1">//code</span>
        <span class="k">break</span><span class="p">;</span>
<span class="p">}</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Esempio:</p>

<div class="language-js highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="cm">/* switch statemeant*/</span>
<span class="kd">const</span> <span class="nx">sport</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="dl">"</span><span class="s2">calcio</span><span class="dl">"</span><span class="p">;</span>

<span class="k">switch</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">sport</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="p">{</span>
    <span class="k">case</span> <span class="dl">"</span><span class="s2">calcio</span><span class="dl">"</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="nx">console</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">log</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="dl">"</span><span class="s2">Amo giocare a calcio</span><span class="dl">"</span><span class="p">);</span>
        <span class="k">break</span><span class="p">;</span>
    <span class="k">case</span> <span class="dl">"</span><span class="s2">tennis</span><span class="dl">"</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="nx">console</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">log</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="dl">"</span><span class="s2">Amo giocare a tennis</span><span class="dl">"</span><span class="p">);</span>
        <span class="k">break</span><span class="p">;</span>
    <span class="nl">default</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="nx">console</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">log</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="dl">"</span><span class="s2">non amo nessuno sportf</span><span class="dl">"</span><span class="p">);</span>
        <span class="k">break</span><span class="p">;</span>
<span class="p">}</span>
<span class="cm">/*
Console:
---------------
Amo giocare a calcio
*/</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>In che occasioni si usa Ã¨ preferibile utilizzare il costrutto <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">switch</code>?<br />
Eâ€™ da preferire quando si hanno opzioni multiple di una un unico <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">key</code> (un tipo di dato qualsiasi) da valutare e tutte le opzioni sono omogenee. In questo caso risulta chiaro e leggibile.</p>

<p>Nel prossimo esempio lo <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">switch/case</code> Ã¨ <em>trasformato</em> in un <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">if/else</code>.</p>

<div class="language-js highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="cm">/* switch statemeant*/</span>

<span class="kd">const</span> <span class="nx">nome</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="dl">"</span><span class="s2">Matteo</span><span class="dl">"</span><span class="p">;</span>
<span class="kd">const</span> <span class="nx">eta</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">15</span><span class="p">;</span>

<span class="k">switch</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="kc">true</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="p">{</span>
    <span class="k">case</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">eta</span> <span class="o">&lt;=</span> <span class="mi">13</span><span class="p">):</span>
        <span class="nx">console</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">log</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">nome</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="dl">"</span><span class="s2"> Ã¨ un bambino</span><span class="dl">"</span><span class="p">);</span>
        <span class="k">break</span><span class="p">;</span>
    <span class="k">case</span> <span class="p">(</span> <span class="nx">eta</span> <span class="o">&gt;</span> <span class="mi">13</span> <span class="o">&amp;&amp;</span> <span class="nx">eta</span> <span class="o">&lt;=</span> <span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">):</span>
        <span class="nx">console</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">log</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">nome</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="dl">"</span><span class="s2"> Ã¨ un ragazzo</span><span class="dl">"</span><span class="p">);</span>
        <span class="k">break</span><span class="p">;</span>
    <span class="nl">default</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="nx">console</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">log</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">nome</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="dl">"</span><span class="s2"> Ã¨ un adulto</span><span class="dl">"</span><span class="p">);</span>
        <span class="k">break</span><span class="p">;</span>
<span class="p">}</span>
<span class="cm">/*
Matteo Ã¨ un ragazzo
*/</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>In questo caso lo <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">switch/case</code> risulta meno chiaro di un <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">if/else</code>. <br />
Eâ€™ importante fin da subito saper utilizzare i costrutti giusti per la situazione giusta.</p>

